==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Murmurous
<hw>Mur"mur*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. L.
<ets>murmuriosus</ets>, OF. <ets>murmuros</ets>.]</ety> <def>Attended
with murmurs; exciting murmurs or complaint; murmuring.</def>
<mark>[Archaic or Poetic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The lime, a summer home of <qex>murmurous</qex> wings.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Murnival</ent>⟦br⟧
